#  Changelog v2.5.38 (MACs on interfaces -- rebuilt for the NetBox 4.x model):
#   - Interface MACs weren't landing because nb_add_interface/nb_add_vm_interface
#     set the interface 'mac_address' field, which NetBox REMOVED in 4.2 (user is
#     on 4.6, so every MAC was silently dropped). MACs are now first-class
#     /dcim/mac-addresses/ objects.
#   - New nb_ensure_mac_address(obj_type,obj_id,mac): idempotently creates the
#     MAC object bound to the interface (assigned_object_type + assigned_object_id)
#     and sets it as the interface's primary_mac_address FK. Handles both
#     dcim.interface and virtualization.vminterface. Reuses an existing MAC on the
#     same interface on re-runs (no duplicates). Errors are surfaced.
#   - nb_add_interface and nb_add_vm_interface no longer send the dead field; they
#     call the helper after the interface exists. Covers all three MAC sources:
#     SNMP ifTable MACs, VM NIC MACs, and now ARP-derived IP MACs.
#   - The MAC for each IP comes from a global ip2mac map the plan builds from
#     every host's ARP/neighbor tables (router+firewall ARP resolve almost every
#     host). ip_assignments now carry 'mac'; the writer stamps it on the IP's
#     interface. Validated: 4.x payload shape, ip2mac coverage on a real capture
#     (every sampled device/VM IP resolved), and ip_assignments now carry MACs.
