#  Changelog v2.5.37 (re-link Hyper-V host Device to its Cluster):
#   - After switching every path to the reconciled writer, Hyper-V host devices
#     (SERVER01/03/04) no longer showed a cluster: nb_upsert_device has no
#     cluster argument and never set the device.cluster FK (the legacy sync did).
#   - Writer now PATCHes device.cluster after upsert, resolving the device's
#     cluster name (== the host's hostname for a Hyper-V host) against the CLU
