#  Changelog v2.5.36 (route ALL sync through the reconciled single writer):
#   - The single writer is now validated end-to-end (devices, VMs, IPs, clusters,
#     cabling), so every menu sync path is repointed to it. Previously the
#     post-Discover 'Sync to NetBox?' prompt (opt 1/3), option 6, and Full Auto
#     (opt 7 + CLI --auto) all called the LEGACY sync_to_netbox -- which invents
#     uplink-<neighbor> interfaces and skips reconciliation/VM-folding/cabling.
#     That was the source of the stray 'uplink' cables.
#   - New run_reconciled_sync() wraps the writer with the same dry-run + confirm
#     as option 9; the interactive prompts (1/3/6) now use it. Full Auto (7 and
#     CLI) calls sync_reconciled_to_netbox directly (unattended, no uplinks).
#   - sync_to_netbox() is left DEFINED but unreferenced by any menu path, so the
#     change is reversible and the legacy code is available if ever needed. No
