#  Changelog v2.5.31 (drop self-referential LLDP links):
#   - The LLDP overlay now skips any neighbor whose name equals the switch's own
#     hostname/serial -- a stack/aggregate interface reporting the switch itself,
#     which is not a real cable. Real switch-to-switch links are unaffected even
#     when the local port is named after the PEER's serial (FortiLink trunks),
#     because the neighbor != the local switch's own id. Validated against the
#     live FortiSwitch capture: the S224EP<->S124FN trunk is kept; a synthetic
#     true self-reference is dropped.
# 
#  Changelog v2.5.30 (switchport cabling: use LLDP, keep the local port):
#   - Diagnosed from real captures: Map Switchports derived links from the FDB
#     (bridge MAC table) + the switch's OWN ARP. That is right for endpoint
#     ports but wrong for uplinks/trunks (a trunk learns every MAC behind it),
#     and remote_ips was always empty because an L2 switch has no ARP table.
#     Meanwhile LLDP -- which states the neighbor and local port directly -- was
#     being captured by the scan but the parser DROPPED the local side, so every
#     switch-to-switch link was unanchored ('local=?').
#   - Parser fix: lldp_neighbors (and cdp) now keep local_port + local_if_index
#     from the probe's 'Origin Interface' / 'Local Interface Index', not just the
#     remote sys_name/port. Verified on real gear: FortiSwitch port1->office-sw,
#     Netgear g8->FortiSwitch:port2 (the uplink the FDB got wrong), etc.
#   - map_switchports overlay: after the FDB walk it pulls LLDP for the switch
#     from the most recent results_*.json and attaches each link to its local
#     port (match local_if_index->ifIndex, else local_port->ifName). Output gains
#     per-port lldp_neighbor / lldp_remote_port + a 'LLDP Neighbor' column and a
#     lldp_source field; falls back silently to FDB-only if no capture exists.
#   - NOTE: requires a fresh scan on 2.5.30+ first (older results_*.json lack the
#     local port), THEN option 4, so the overlay has anchored LLDP to consume.
# 
#  Changelog v2.5.29 (Map Switchports only tried 'public' / no SNMPv3):
#   - map_switchports() took only the FIRST community (community=get_communities
#     _for | head -1, usually 'public') and its inline snmpwalk was hardcoded to
#     -v2c, so a switch on a non-default community or SNMPv3-only (e.g. the
#     FortiGate / FortiSwitches) returned no interface/MAC data at all.
#   - Fix: the full credential store is now passed to the walker -- ordered v2c
#     communities (incl. per-IP override) plus v3 USM creds. It probes sysDescr
#     with each (v2c first, then v3 authPriv/authNoPriv) and uses the first that
#     answers for every walk; prints the chosen auth. The Cisco per-VLAN MAC
#     trick now adapts to the working cred (v2c community@vid, or v3 'vlan-<id>'
#     SNMP context). Mirrors the main scan's credential handling. Stub-tested:
#     selects a non-first v2c community, falls through to v3, and exits cleanly
#     when nothing authenticates.
