#  Changelog v2.5.23 (fix: custom fields STILL partial -- memory_gb + resilient patch):
#   - Symptom: only cpu_model/cpu_cores/memory_gb populated (the 3 fields the
#     old 2.5.16-2.5.18 writer set, with memory_gb='31.41' as TEXT); every field
#     added in 2.5.19 stayed blank -> the full custom_fields PATCH was STILL
#     failing. Cause: memory_gb already holds a text value, so NetBox refuses to
#     recast it to integer; the 2.5.22 type-reconcile couldn't change it, the
#     writer kept sending an integer, and the whole PATCH 400'd (one bad field
#     drops them all).
#   - Fix 1: memory_gb is now a TEXT field and the value is sent as a string
#     (e.g. '31.92'). This matches the existing type everywhere -- no risky
#     type change, always populates. memory_mb stays an integer for precision.
#   - Fix 2 (defensive, permanent): the device custom_fields PATCH is now
#     resilient. If the bundled PATCH is rejected, each field is applied
#     individually so the rest still land, and the offending field is logged by
#     name. No single bad field can ever blank the whole set again.
#   - nb_api returns the response body (exit 0 even on HTTP 400); success is
#     detected by the presence of .id in the response.
#
#  Changelog v2.5.22 (fix: empty device custom fields on hardware-bearing hosts):
#   - THE actual cause of empty custom fields (even with collector hardware
#     present): nb_ensure_custom_field was get-or-create and never reconciled
#     an existing field's TYPE. The 2.5.16-2.5.18 writer created memory_gb as
#     'text'; testing against that same NetBox, 2.5.19's 'ensure integer' was a
#     no-op (field already existed), so memory_gb stayed 'text'. The writer then
#     sent an integer to it, which 400s the ENTIRE custom_fields PATCH -- and
#     the error was swallowed (|| true) -- so EVERY device custom field silently
#     dropped. (Not a data problem; the collector hardware was there.)
#   - Fix: nb_ensure_custom_field now PATCHes an existing field's type to match
#     when it differs (best-effort; safe because the failed patches meant the
#     field had no values to conflict). On the next option-9 run it self-heals
#     memory_gb text->integer, and the full custom_fields PATCH then lands.
#   - Confirmed the collector script emits per-VM DiskBytes + Disks[] and the
#     importer carries them as hyperv_vms, so 2.5.21's VirtualDisk creation has
#     data on the collector-import flow (no WinRM required).
