#  Changelog v2.5.12 (standalone collector for WinRM-closed machines):
#   - Added generate_collector_script() + Import menu option 8. Emits a
#     standalone, READ-ONLY netbox-collector.ps1 that runs on ANY Windows
#     machine (workstation or Hyper-V host) with NO WinRM and NO NetBox access,
#     and writes ONE merged JSON file (host hardware + physical disks + NICs/IPs,
#     and -- if Hyper-V -- VMs with vCPU/memory/disks/NIC MACs + neighbor table).
#   - Motivation: Windows workstations generally do not (and should not) have
#     WinRM open, so the WinRM probes can never reach them. The standalone script
#     is hand-carried to those hosts, run locally, and the resulting JSON is
#     brought back and ingested -- the same data path that 2.5.9's "save PS1 for
#     manual execution" mode provided, but collect-only (no NetBox writes).
#   - Uses the EXACT PS_BASE + PS_HYPERV collection bodies (validated byte-for-
#     byte against the embedded source), so a host collected by hand and one
#     collected over WinRM produce identical JSON. Cmdlets are all Get-* only;
#     zero writes. Purely additive: sync_to_netbox, import_hyperv_powershell,
#     merge_host_data and probe_ssh are untouched.
#   - This is step 1 of the single-writer re-architecture: collector emits JSON
#     -> (next) import path + reconciler consumption -> (next) sync_to_netbox
#     consumes the reconciled model and the PS1's direct NetBox writes retire.
