#  Changelog v2.6.1 (VM detail + custom-field fixes from first live sync):
#   - BUG 1 (memory blank on all VMs): PS_HYPERV read $vm.MemoryStartupBytes,
#     which is NOT a property of the Get-VM object (returned 0). Corrected to
#     $vm.MemoryStartup. VM memory now populates on the next capture.
#   - BUG 2 (vCPU/memory blank on IP-MATCHED VMs): the reconciler's matched-VM
#     branch set vm_name/host/cluster/state but not vm_cpu/vm_mem_bytes (only
#     the synthesized branch did), so .5/.14/.30/... synced with empty CPU and
#     memory while synthesized VMs showed them. Matched VMs now carry
#     vm_cpu/vm_mem_bytes from the inventory entry.
#   - BUG 3 (custom fields missing on VMs AND servers): discovered_ports and
#     discovery_methods were scoped to dcim.device only and patched only in
#     the device branch (the VM branch returned before it). Now: (a)
#     nb_ensure_custom_field accepts a comma-separated object_types list and
#     MERGES scope onto an existing field, so the fields cover both
#     dcim.device and virtualization.virtualmachine; (b) the VM sync branch
#     patches discovered_ports/discovery_methods onto the VM. Devices
#     (incl. the Hyper-V servers, which are Server-role) keep populating via
#     the device branch, now guaranteed the field is scoped to dcim.device.
#   - Disk: not yet collected (Get-VM exposes no disk size); a future change
#     can add Get-VMHardDiskDrive/Get-VHD and create NetBox virtual-disks.
