#  Changelog v2.4.3 (false-vendor fix from nmap fingerprint dump):
#   - merge_host_data(): nmap 'fingerprint-strings' (a raw dump of the full
#     service response, including arbitrary HTML bodies) is no longer fed to
#     vendor/role keyword matching. Modern web UIs embed the CSS font
#     '-apple-system' and meta tag 'apple-mobile-web-app-capable', which the
#     loose 'apple' keyword matched -> any web-managed device could be
#     mislabeled manufacturer Apple (seen on 192.168.0.2). Curated scripts
#     (http-title, snmp-info, nbstat, rdp-ntlm-info, ssl-cert) still feed it.
