#  Changelog v2.3.7 (capture RustScan ports; broaden OS-misfingerprint guard):
#   - probe_nmap() parser: RustScan/discovery-found TCP ports are now UNIONED
#     into host['ports'], passed as argv[3]. RustScan reliably finds open
#     ports via fast SYN scan, but the -sV/-O/script deep scan still stalls
#     and aborts on host-firewalled boxes, so those ports were being fed to
#     nmap's -p and then LOST (empty open_ports -> Endpoint, despite the log
#     showing 'RustScan found ports: 135,3389,...'). Now they always land in
#     the record; nmap only enriches them with service/version when it can.
#   - merge_host_data(): Windows-exclusive-port OS override no longer gates
#     on 'linux' -- it now overrides ANY non-Windows guess (also seen:
#     'Allen Bradley MicroLogix 1100 PLC') to 'Microsoft Windows'.
