#  Changelog v2.3.6 (filtered Windows hosts: reliable port discovery +
#  OS-misfingerprint guard):
#   - probe_nmap(): added a FAST nmap discovery pass (-Pn, no -sV/scripts/-O,
#     30s timeout) used when RustScan finds nothing. The deep -sV/-O/script
#     scan then runs ONLY against confirmed-open ports. Previously, running
#     -sV + 14 NSE scripts against ~40 ports on a host-firewalled Windows box
#     stalled past --host-timeout 90s and nmap aborted the host, yielding an
#     empty result (Endpoint). Mirrors a manual 'nmap -Pn <ip>' (<10s).
#   - merge_host_data(): nmap commonly mis-fingerprints filtered Windows
#     hosts as 'Linux 2.6.x'. When a Windows-EXCLUSIVE port is open
#     (msrpc 135, RDP 3389, WinRM 5985/6, vmrdp 2179, MSMQ 1801/2103-2107,
#     WSD 5357) the Linux guess is overridden to 'Microsoft Windows', fixing
#     role (Workstation/Server) and manufacturer (Microsoft). NetBIOS/SMB
#     (137-139,445) are excluded from this set since Samba serves them on
#     Linux -- real Linux/Samba hosts stay Linux/Server.
